cmm5mppf300ah2ut5svq30zus	cmm5mpl7e00032ut599t7cdqn	1 0 8 I N T E R M A R I N E 9 5 Chegando ao local de destino 15. Ao lançar ou recolher âncora, cuide para que o cabo ou corrente não se aproxime dos hélices. 16. Se for necessário deixar a embarcação ancorada e sem ninguém a bordo, esteja cer- to de que ela estará bem segura, inclusive no caso de uma rápida piora nas condições me- teorológicas. Procure manter contato visual. 17. O uso das capas de para brisa e vidros laterais é obrigatório com a embarcação atracada ou ancorada para evitar danos nos móveis internos, tecidos e equipamentos instalados na sala. ATENÇÃO! 17. Em períodos em que a embarcação for permanecer na água sem ninguém a bordo e sem vigia, esteja certo de que as baterias estão carregadas, as bombas de porão e seus automáticos estão funcio- nando, e feche todas as válvulas das en- tradas e saídas de água junto ao casco. ATENÇÃO! 18. Ao colocar as defensas no costado, NÃO posicione-as sobre as janelas de vidro do casco. Há risco de quebrar o vi- dro.	108	186	[0.053681,0.052456,0.052864,0.035719,0.040822,0.032862,0.058988,0.019595,0.056947,0.046945,0.060212,0.047558,0.058171,0.019595,0.060825,0.049803,0.042659,0.04919,0.056538,0.036332,0.056334,0.036536,0.041434,0.053885,0.083277,0.052048,0.057967,0.036944,0.054293,0.032862,0.058375,0.034495,0.054497,0.064295,0.066744,0.051027,0.046945,0.066948,0.049395,0.052864,0.050823,0.066336,0.062253,0.048374,0.065315,0.05266,0.074296,0.046945,0.051232,0.050007,0.063478,0.090421,0.047966,0.060008,0.067764,0.079603,0.067356,0.063478,0.05164,0.075112,0.047762,0.056538,0.052864,0.022452,0.047966,0.043679,0.065723,0.052456,0.064703,0.046129,0.065519,0.090012,0.046129,0.090625,0.072663,0.068785,0.050619,0.048986,0.056334,0.050415,0.053273,0.060008,0.055926,0.057559,0.081032,0.069601,0.045312,0.076745,0.035515,0.050007,0.056538,0.052864,0.048986,0.045516,0.048986,0.047149,0.063886,0.050619,0.065315,0.06307,0.050007,0.062458,0.049599,0.050415,0.063682,0.051436,0.053273,