cmm5mppfu00al2ut5vtf21wbl	cmm5mpl7e00032ut599t7cdqn	1 1 0 I N T E R M A R I N E 9 5 Emergências 1. Esteja preparado para agir em ocasiões de emergência. Tente formular planos de ação para os diferentes tipos de emergências, e observe as experiências que outras pessoas tiveram em momentos difíceis no mar. Lem- bre-se que em situações críticas o tempo é fundamental para evitar piores consequên- cias. 2. Noções de primeiros socorros e uma cai- xa de medicamentos compatível para essas ocasiões, também são muito úteis. PERIGO! 3. Oriente aos passageiros, assim que entrarem a bordo, sobre o local em que está guardado o material de salvatagem / extintores e como utilizá-los numa emer- gência. PERIGO! 4. O Monóxido de Carbono (CO) é um gás que não tem cheiro, não tem cor e é extremamente tóxico. Ele é produzido na combustão que ocorre nos motores e gerador. Mantenha os ambientes ven- tilados e inspecione frequentemente se há vazamento nos mangotes dos escapes dos motores e gerador. 5. Cuidado com a decisão de nadar até a praia ou qualquer outro	110	188	[0.053899,0.046843,0.051547,0.035083,0.051547,0.069774,0.056642,0.021363,0.043707,0.052723,0.05527,0.018815,0.054878,0.045471,0.044099,0.049979,0.05723,0.045667,0.039591,0.047235,0.056838,0.050175,0.040375,0.049195,0.059778,0.050763,0.057818,0.034887,0.050371,0.050567,0.038023,0.048019,0.038807,0.064286,0.086042,0.067814,0.058994,0.08663,0.049587,0.063698,0.048607,0.047627,0.056642,0.031555,0.050959,0.05429,0.048607,0.054095,0.065462,0.048019,0.047823,0.061934,0.060562,0.035083,0.061542,0.091725,0.058798,0.06507,0.047431,0.050175,0.064482,0.058406,0.065658,0.031751,0.090745,0.06017,0.050175,0.050371,0.057034,0.063502,0.047039,0.06311,0.064286,0.046451,0.064286,0.065658,0.018815,0.090549,0.048411,0.059386,0.064678,0.065658,0.078986,0.045863,0.057622,0.040375,0.057426,0.055662,0.039983,0.041551,0.047823,0.048411,0.052135,0.051351,0.075066,0.056838,0.063306,0.063894,0.058602,0.051939,0.048803,0.057818,0.048803,0.060366,0.050763,